<TITLE> Govt plans doubling food stock capacity </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 8 (bdnews24.com)  Facilities for storage of additional 7 lakh tons of food grains will be built in three years to raise government's stock capacity, food and disaster management minister said Tuesday. "We'll build the new storages to reserve more food in an effort to fight any future food crisis," Abdur Razzak told reporters after the Executive Committee of the National Economic Council (ECNEC) approved two projects for constructing storages of 2.19 lakh tonscapacity. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina presided over the ECNEC meeting. Razzak said the government is expecting to raise the storage capacity from the existing 14 lakh ton to 30 lakh ton within 2021. The minister said 162 storages with a total capacity of 1.35 lakh tons would be built across the country at a cost of Tk 283 crore. Of them, 108 storages will have 1000 ton capacity each and 54 will be of 500 ton capacity each. Under another project, 91 storages with a total capacity of 84,000 ton will be built at Halishohor in Chittagong at a cost of Tk 219 crore. Razzak said another two projects of 1.6 lakh ton storage capacity are already under construction. Currently, 6 lakh tons of food grains are in government stock, he said. bdn
